<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="80" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="43" pageNumber="80">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="43" pageNumber="80">-As for genus above. Size (in mm): total length males 12-14, females 18-20. Epiphallus as in Fig. 310.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="80" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="43" pageNumber="80">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="43" pageNumber="80">-Terri-graminicole, on dry stony hillsides and in gullies with short grass, scattered bushes and aloes, acacias as well as other shrubs and small trees. Frequently found on open ground but never far from shelter of vegetation where it hides on disturbance.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
